HEADWORD: Chain wheel
<hw>Chain" wheel`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <sn>1.</sn> <def>A chain pulley, or
sprocket wheel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An inversion of the chain pump, by which it becomes
a motor driven by water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chainwork</ent>⟦br⟧
